featured_reviews.review_id:
Makka  masjid is also known as Masjid-i Jehan Numa.

Makka Masjid is one of the largest mosques in sardar shahar

It was established in 1956.

Makka Masjid consists of 4 minarets each 40 meters high.

The mosque is made up of red sandstone and marble.

The mosque can hold a capacity of more than 5000 people.

There are 3 domes on the terrace of the mosque which are surrounded by the 4 minarets.

Makka Masjid is a magnificent place to visit and attracts a lot of tourists from everywhere.

featured_reviews.review_translated_text:
Respected teacher friends,
Saturday - No Bag Day has been announced as an innovation for students in the Rajasthan budget. In this regard, the cartoon published in Dainik Bhaskar has raised questions on the efficiency of all government schools and teachers. This so-called newspaper, which survives on pieces of advertising from private schools, has in the past also published news with a negative attitude towards government schools.
While on one hand we are seeing that the confidence of parents towards government schools has increased in the last few years, Bhamashah and the general public are making efforts to make the schools well-equipped, and teachers are working to improve the educational and co-scholastic level of the schools. Efforts are being made continuously. On the other hand, such negativity is being spread.
We should unite and oppose this, such news hurts our self-esteem.

All teacher organizations will have to stand up in solidarity and protest against this.

 A distressed teacher
